                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.01,
                                "byte_start": 87428,
                                "byte_stop": 131523,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 00-9280 Kelly against South Carolina will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.01,
                        "stop": 272.431,
                        "byte_start": 131523,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.01,
                                "stop": 17.111,
                                "byte_start": 131523,
                                "byte_stop": 155973,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the Supreme Court of South Carolina."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.111,
                                "stop": 26.107,
                                "byte_start": 155973,
                                "byte_stop": 191918,
                                "text": "In 1996, the South Carolina jury convicted the petitioner William Kelly who agrees with the kidnapping and robbery and murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.107,
                                "stop": 38.7,
                                "byte_start": 191918,
                                "byte_stop": 242282,
                                "text": "During the separate sentencing proceedings, the prosecutor presented evidence that Kelly had fashioned crude knives while he was in jail and took part in an attempt to take a hostage and to escape."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.7,
                                "stop": 50.268,
                                "byte_start": 242282,
                                "byte_stop": 288571,
                                "text": "On cross examination of the psychologist the prosecutor brought out evidence of Kelly\u0027s childhood sadism as well of his recurrent homicidal fantasies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.268,
                                "stop": 68.497,
                                "byte_start": 288571,
                                "byte_stop": 361505,
                                "text": "After presentation of the evidence but before the closing arguments, Kelly\u0027s counsel relied on our decision and Simmons v. South Carolina in requesting a so-called Simmons instruction to the jury, that if Kelly received the sentence of life imprisonment, he would be ineligible for parole."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.497,
                                "stop": 84.749,
                                "byte_start": 361505,
                                "byte_stop": 426497,
                                "text": "The prosecutor objected on the ground that he was not going to argue future dangerousness and the trial judge denied the request of charge ruling the State\u0027s evidenciary submission went not to future dangerousness but only to Kelly\u0027s character and characteristics."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.749,
                                "stop": 101.196,
                                "byte_start": 426497,
                                "byte_stop": 492221,
                                "text": "In his closing argument, the prosecutor compared Kelly to a notorious serial killer, characterizing him variously as Bloody Billy, the butcher of Batesburg and as a little more dangerous because he was intelligent and quick-witted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.196,
                                "stop": 106.193,
                                "byte_start": 492221,
                                "byte_stop": 512284,
                                "text": "Thereafter the trial judge charged the jury without giving a Simmons instruction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.193,
                                "stop": 110.761,
                                "byte_start": 512284,
                                "byte_stop": 530569,
                                "text": "The jury recommended the death sentence and the trial court imposed it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.761,
                                "stop": 114.472,
                                "byte_start": 530569,
                                "byte_stop": 545407,
                                "text": "The Supreme Court of South Carolina affirmed the conviction and sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.472,
                                "stop": 120.935,
                                "byte_start": 545407,
                                "byte_stop": 571216,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we reverse the judgment of the State Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.935,
                                "stop": 130.829,
                                "byte_start": 571216,
                                "byte_stop": 610817,
                                "text": "In upholding the trial court\u0027s refusal to instruct the jury on the parole ineligibility, the State Supreme Court advanced two rationales."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.829,
                                "stop": 145.058,
                                "byte_start": 610817,
                                "byte_stop": 667764,
                                "text": "One ground given by the court was that Simmons was inapplicable to South Carolina\u0027s new sentencing scheme because life without possibility of parole was not the only legally available sentencing alternative to death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.058,
                                "stop": 149.328,
                                "byte_start": 667764,
                                "byte_stop": 684796,
                                "text": "We invalidated this ground in last term in Shafer v. South Carolina."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.328,
                                "stop": 166.561,
                                "byte_start": 684796,
                                "byte_stop": 753759,
                                "text": "There we held it well a capital defendant in South Carolina can under some circumstances receive a sentence less than life imprisonment, under the state\u0027s scheme, a jury makes a sentencing recommendation only if the the jury\u0027s first find one or more aggravating factors."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.561,
                                "stop": 174.026,
                                "byte_start": 753759,
                                "byte_stop": 783539,
                                "text": "In the event that they do find an aggravating circumstance, their recommendations can be only death or life without parole."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.026,
                                "stop": 181.908,
                                "byte_start": 783539,
                                "byte_stop": 815095,
                                "text": "Thus, the State\u0027s Supreme Court\u0027s reasoning about the availability of a third sentencing alternative cannot be accepted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.908,
                                "stop": 228.576,
                                "byte_start": 815095,
                                "byte_stop": 1001818,
                                "text": "A second ground given by the State\u0027s Supreme Court in this case for holding no Simmons instruction was required was that Kelly\u0027s future dangerousness was not at issue, a conclusion that is in sharp conflict with the evidence presented in the arguments made at Kelly\u0027s trial, the state court failed to recognize that evidence may have a tendency to prove future dangerousness even though that same evidence can support other inferences or be described in other terms, and the State Court likewise can overlook the fact that the prosecutor accentuated the clear implication of future dangerousness raised by the evidence when his argument invited the jury to conclude that Kelly was a dangerous and bloody butcher."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.576,
                                "stop": 241.478,
                                "byte_start": 1001818,
                                "byte_stop": 1053436,
                                "text": "We find no merit in the State\u0027s alternative argument here that Kelly\u0027s jury was not confused about the matter of his parole ineligibility because the jury did not request further instructions from the trial judge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.478,
                                "stop": 262.923,
                                "byte_start": 1053436,
                                "byte_stop": 1139222,
                                "text": "A judge\u0027s obligation to give adequate explanation of the law does not depend on expressions of perplexity by the jury and there is no reason to believe that Kelly\u0027s jury was aware of relatively recent changes in South Carolina Law that categorically preclude parole for capital defendants sentenced to life imprisonment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 262.923,
                                "stop": 272.431,
                                "byte_start": 1139222,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed a dissenting opinion which Justice Kennedy has joined; Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion which Justice Scalia has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
